name: Yakima Community Vaccine Center
info: ***PFIZER VACCINATIONS*** !!!!VACUNAS DE PFIZER!!! Enter fairgrounds through Gate 15 off of Pacific Avenue. Be prepared to show confirmation of your appointment or you may experience a slightly longer wait. Masks are required. Please wear clothing which allows access to your shoulder. Vaccinations at this site are reserved for people who live and/or work in Washington State. All Minors age 17 and Under must be accompanied by a parent. Ingresar por la puerta 15 en la avenida Pacífico. Se requieren máscaras. Por favor, use ropa que permita acceso a su brazo. Las vacunas en este sitio están reservadas para las personas que viven o trabajan en el estado de Washington. Todos los menores de 17 años o menos deben ir con su padres.*** PFIZER VACCINATIONS*** !!!!VACUNAS DE PFIZER!!!
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Walla Walla County HD- COVID Provider
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
**THIS CLINIC IS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY FOR 1st & 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS for all qualifying individuals aged 12 years & over. Parental/Guardian consent is required for 12 – 17 year olds, parent/guardian consent and signature can be completed on-site or in the final screen of the online registration process. Janssen (Johnson & Johnson) vaccine is also available for people 18 years and older. This clinic is at the Providence Southgate Medical Park main building (the former Walla Walla General Hospital) 1025 South 2nd Ave. Participants are advised to stay to their right as they enter the campus and proceed to the main entrance, instead of going to Urgent Care. COVID vaccine is not available in Urgent Care.
Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
We look forward to seeing you. Thanks for keeping Walla Walla well.

** ESTA CLÍNICA ES CON CITA SOLAMENTE PARA LAS VACUNAS DE LA PRIMERA DOSIS DE PFIZER para personas calificadas de 12 años en Adelante.  Se requiere el consentimiento de los padres / tutores para los jóvenes de 12 - 17 años, las firmas y el consentimiento en la pantalla de registro final.  La vacuna Janssen (Johnson & Johnson) también está disponible para personas mayores de 18 años.** Esto será en el edificio principal de Providence Southgate Medical Park, (antes conocido como el Hospital General de Walla Walla)1025 Sur 2nd ave.  Se recomienda a los participantes que se mantengan a su derecha al ingresar y que se dirijan a la entrada principal, en lugar de ir a Atención de Urgencia.  La Vacuna COVID no está disponible en Atención de Urgencias. **
El cubre bocas es requerido. Si no tiene un cubre bocas, se le proporcionará una.  
Esperamos verlo. Gracias por cuidar a Walla Walla.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: Capital Mall - 625 Black Lake Boulevard Southwest, Olympia WA, 98502
info: This is a single-dose Johnson & Johnson clinic being held at Capital Mall, 625 Black Lake Blvd SW, Olympia WA, 98502 for anyone age 18 and older from 12pm-8pm.  We will be located inside the mall, closest to the Sephora end of the mall and next to the Buckle store. Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers, if needed. • Please arrive at your scheduled appointment time. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: Timberline High School - 6120 Mullen Rd SE, Lacey WA, 98503
info:
This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older. 

• This is a walk-in clinic at Timberline High School located at 6120 Mullen Rd SE, Lacey WA, 98503 • All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with warm layers. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
